The paper investigates the role of context in a neural language model, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) research. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves analyzing the model's behavior and performance, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to improve the model's performance, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses a specific type of neural network (LSTM), which is a common tool in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses two standard datasets, which could be related to cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the datasets involve visual data.
